From: Stefan Reinauer <stefan.reinauer@coreboot.org>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 15:10:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] build: statically link Windows plugin dependencies

The Windows plugin is loaded from WinUAE's plugin directory. If that
directory already contains old or wrong-architecture copies of GLib,
zlib, winpthread, or similar MinGW/MSYS2 DLLs, the Windows loader can
pick those first and reject qemu-uae.dll with ERROR_BAD_EXE_FORMAT.

Pass QEMU's --static option on Windows hosts so Meson and pkg-config
prefer static MinGW/MSYS2 libraries and the plugin can be distributed as
a single DLL.
---
 configure-qemu-uae | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configure-qemu-uae b/configure-qemu-uae
index ad9212c452..591df4296c 100755
--- a/configure-qemu-uae
+++ b/configure-qemu-uae
@@ -29,6 +29,8 @@ MINGW*|MSYS*|CLANG*|UCRT*)
             export CXX=g++
         fi
     fi
+    # Keep the Windows plugin independent of sidecar MSYS2 DLLs.
+    set -- --static "$@"
     ;;
 *)
     EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -fPIC"
